Sentencas: Electrochemical performance, impedance spectroscopy and carbon tolerance analysis show, for the first time, that molybdenum carbide has great potential for application as anode catalyst in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Evaluation of molybdenum carbide as anode catalyst for proton-conducting hydrogen and ethane solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ethylene and stable power density are coproduced from ethane in proton-conducting SOFC with molybdenum carbide as anode catalyst and BCZY as electrolyte.
Titulo: Evaluation of molybdenum carbide as anode catalyst for proton-conducting hydrogen and ethane solid oxide fuel cells
